Fake Product Identification using Blockchain








Repository

https://github.com/Hannah-art-dot/BlockAuth Products

Project Description

BlockAuth Products is a blockchain-based platform designed to verify authentic products and detect counterfeit goods. Using smart contracts on a local blockchain, the system ensures secure, transparent, and tamper-proof product verification.

This project demonstrates how blockchain can enhance product authenticity and supply chain trust.

Features

âœ… Add and verify products on the blockchain

âœ… Detect counterfeit products in real-time

âœ… Secure, tamper-proof product records

âœ… Integration with MetaMask for blockchain account management

âœ… User-friendly web interface

Project Workflow
flowchart LR
A[User visits website] --> B[Connect MetaMask wallet]
B --> C[Add or verify product]
C --> D[Smart contract on local blockchain]
D --> E[Blockchain records updated]
E --> F[User receives verification result]


Workflow: User â†’ MetaMask â†’ Smart Contract â†’ Blockchain â†’ Verification Result

Required Packages

Truffle: v5.6.7

Ganache: v7.5.0

Solidity: v0.5.16 (solc-js)

Node.js: v15.8.0

Web3.js: v1.7.4

npm: 7.5.1

Other Requirements

Chromium-based browser (e.g., Chrome)

MetaMask browser extension

Setup Process

Clone the project

git clone https://github.com/Hannah-art-dot/BlockAuth\ Products.git


Install dependencies

cd "BlockAuth Products"
npm install


Compile smart contracts

truffle compile


Setup Ganache (local blockchain)

Create a new workspace

Add truffle-config.js

Set port to 7545 (must match truffle-config.js)

Configure MetaMask

Add a new test network:

Network ID: 5777

RPC Server: http://127.0.0.1:8545

Chain ID: 1337

Import an account using a private key from Ganache

Deploy smart contracts

truffle migrate


Start the development server

npm run dev


Connect MetaMask

Login and connect to localhost:3000

Interact with the website and test BlockAuth Products features
